(137, 'Spring: Core annotations', 'Spring dependency injection is one of the core features of Spring Framework that enables application-wide instantiation, management, and assembly of beans. To use these features we have to go through the annotations provided in the org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation and org.springframework.context.annotation package. They can be considered the core annotations of Spring that we will learn together shortly.', '<p><a href=\"#h_3313677111626245790513\">1. Spring: Core annotations</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_165602665181626245794487\">1.1. @Autowired</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_222868653341626245798351\">1.2. @Bean</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_239708568491626245802759\">1.3. @Qualifiter</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_693758691631626245806975\">1.4. @Required</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_531598239761626245811383\">1.5. @Value</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_90118668881626245816375\">1.6. @DependsOn</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_343270838991626245820783\">1.7. @Lazy</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_8501661611091626245825231\">1.8. @Primary</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_4082030701181626245829919\">1.9. @Scope</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_9515982721261626245835567\">2. Context Configuration Annotations</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_3717648871331626245840599\">2.1. @Profile</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_9257015351391626245845886\">2.2. @Import</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_4524627861561626245856087\">2.3. @ImportResource</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_2677907821691626245864190\">2.4. @PropertySource</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_5138240981781626245879101\">2.5. @PropertySources</a></p>', 'spring-core-annotations', 'imageblogs/PwgodMM8IS3BTjuL6UudAF0rBtaRgRuhFizqYAPj.jpg', 'Spring, Core annotations, properties, bean, configuration, corresponding data, Spring dependency injection', 4, 'active', '2023-02-17 01:10:55', '2023-02-17 01:10:55', 2, 0),
(138, 'HTML and HTML5: What are the differences? HTML5\'s strengths', 'Historically, the markup language was inspired by the process of manuscript marking-up through printer instructions, taken from handwritten markups. HTML is the most famous markup language used. In the last few years, an update to this language, HTML5 was published. In this article, Hachinet will explain the difference between HTML and HTML5.', '<p><a href=\"#h_695369127301626251727732\">1. What is HTML?</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_337439137601626251745340\">2. The difference between HTML and HTML5</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_60944616741626251752244\">3. HTML5\'s strengths for programmers</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_468952910871626251756804\">3.1. Persistent error handling</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_443923083991626251766884\">3.2. Improved semantics for elements</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_6285164571101626251771691\">3.3. Increase web application compatibility</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_6711120631201626251776996\">3.4. Easier to build&nbsp;mobile&nbsp;websites</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_4195875991291626251782548\">3.5. Canvas element</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_7476445161371626251788411\">3.6. The Menu element</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_6779836921441626251793852\">3.7. Data Attributes can be customized</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_8489805921501626251804404\">3.8. No longer has Cookies</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_2575549131591626251834621\"><span id=\"Thu-thuat-HTML5\">4. HTML5\'s tips and tricks</span></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#h_1031056221631626251840215\"><span id=\"Uu-diem-cua-HTML5-cho-nguoi-dung-cuoi\">5. Advantages of HTML5 for End Users</span></a></p>', 'html-and-html5-what-are-the-differences-html5-s-strengths', 'imageblogs/PwgodMM8IS3BTjuL6UudAF0rBtaRgRuhFizqYAPj.jpg', NULL, 4, 'active', '2023-02-17 01:10:55', '2023-02-17 01:10:55', 2, 0),
